# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# @faraday-academy/cli (agent-edu) — environment
#
# This repo is a LOCAL CLI scaffolder with zero runtime dependencies. It needs
# no API keys, database, or secrets: `faraday new` / `faraday check` run with
# nothing set here. Copy to `.env.local` only if you want the one optional knob.
#   cp .env.example .env.local
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Skip `pnpm install` after scaffolding a lesson (equivalent to the
# `faraday new --skip-install` flag). Handy in CI / tests. "1" enables it;
# unset or any other value = install runs. (src/cli.mjs)
FARADAY_SKIP_INSTALL=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOT for this repo — env for the lessons it GENERATES
#
# A lesson scaffolded with `faraday new --tutor` needs a Vercel AI Gateway key
# at runtime. That belongs in the *generated lesson's* own `.env.local`, not
# here — the scaffold ships its own template at
# templates/addon-tutor/env.example (→ becomes `env.example` in the lesson):
#
#   AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=    # local BYO key; on Vercel, auth is via OIDC (no key)
#
# The tutor's model is a source constant (MODEL_ID in workflows/tutor-agent.ts),
# not an env var.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
